- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of model predictive control (MPC) and analyzes the closed-loop stability of the combined plant-optimizer system. 
- cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper proposes a suboptimal MPC method that uses an estimate of the optimal solution and updates it at each sampling instance. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, the use of MPC and optimization techniques may be relevant to this sub-category. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the use of the semismooth predictor-corrector method to implement suboptimal MPC, which is a numerical optimization technique. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category is less likely, but the paper does mention the use of small gain arguments to derive sufficient conditions for closed-loop stability, which may be relevant to networked systems.
